# Tower FDE Workflow Agent — Agent Skills

## Project Context
LangGraph-based workflow agent for a Forward Deployed Engineer at Tower.
Read `MEMORY_BANK.md` for full architecture decisions and current progress.

## Skills

### discovery-node
Build or modify a discovery subgraph node.
- Location: `src/graph/discovery/`
- Pattern: async function, takes `CustomerState`, returns dict
- Uses `get_llm("strong")` for generation, `get_llm("fast")` for classification
- May use `interrupt()` for HITL approval
- May use `retrieve_similar()` from `src/kb/store.py` for KB retrieval

### poc-node
Build or modify a PoC/demo prep subgraph node.
- Location: `src/graph/poc/`
- Same patterns as discovery-node
- `competitive_positioning` uses Tavily via `src/integrations/tavily_search.py`

### proposal-node
Build or modify a proposal subgraph node.
- Location: `src/graph/proposal/`
- `compile_document` is a tool node (no LLM), uses `src/integrations/gdrive.py`

### followup-node
Build or modify a follow-up subgraph node.
- Location: `src/graph/followup/`
- `extract_product_feedback` feeds the product feedback loop
- `update_health_score` uses Haiku, no interrupt

### kb-operation
Work with the ChromaDB knowledge base.
- Store: `src/kb/store.py` — ChromaDB client, 5 collections, `retrieve_similar()`
- Indexer: `src/kb/indexer.py` — post-approval auto-indexing
- Embeddings: local `all-MiniLM-L6-v2`, never API

### ui-component
Build or modify the FastAPI + HTMX UI.
- Routes: `src/ui/routes.py`
- Templates: `src/ui/templates/` (Jinja2)
- Approval flow: approve/edit/reject via `Command(resume=...)` on LangGraph

### integration
Work with external services.
- Gmail: `src/integrations/gmail.py` (v2 only, not in v1)
- Google Drive: `src/integrations/gdrive.py`
- Tavily: `src/integrations/tavily_search.py`
- OpenRouter: `src/llm/models.py`

### test-fixture
Create or modify test fixtures.
- Dummy emails: `tests/fixtures/emails/` (JSON)
- Graph tests: `tests/test_graph/`
- KB tests: `tests/test_kb/`
- Mock LLM: `tests/conftest.py`

## Rules
- Always read `MEMORY_BANK.md` before starting work
- Use OpenRouter, never Anthropic direct
- No live Gmail in v1 — use dummy fixtures
- Update `MEMORY_BANK.md` after completing a milestone
